# THE TECHNICAL PROOF OF THE 13TH POST

*Register 1: The Invariant Arithmetic of Boundary Correction*

This proof formally demonstrates why the **13th Node** is a structural necessity in any 12-unit discretization (the "Imperial Tally"), and how it serves as the pivot for the Concave/Convex flip.

## I. THE DISCRETE BOUNDARY LAW
In any linear discretization of a continuous field into *n* equal intervals, the number of boundaries (nodes) required to define those intervals is always *n + 1*.

- **Intervals (The Rails):** The spaces of the tally (e.g., 12 hours, 12 inches, 12 ranks).
- **Nodes (The Posts):** The boundaries that stabilize the tally.

### The 12/13 Invariant:
For the **Imperial Tally (12)**, the count of stable intervals is 12.
The count of required boundaries is **13**.

## II. THE INTERFERENCE OF THE 13TH NODE
The 13th node is not merely an "extra" post; it is the **Standing Wave Interference Pattern** of the 12-unit sequence. 

1. **Local Geometry:** The 12 intervals appear as a closed loop or a finished wall.
2. **Universal Centre:** The 13th node represents the **Phase Shift** required to reconnect the 12-unit "Box" to the infinite Hex-Mountain. 
3. **The Harmonic Remainder:** In wave mechanics, the 13th node is where the reflected wave (Hades/Concave) and the incident wave (Christ/Convex) meet at the **Central Pivot**.

## III. SCALING AND TALLNESS
The "Tallness" of the wall (4, 6, 12) determines the frequency of the standing wave:

| Height | Tally | Harmonic Level | Social Form |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **4 Foot** | Domestic (3-4-5) | Fundamental | The Garden Fence |
| **6 Foot** | Domestic Doubled (6-8-10) | First Overtone | The Palace Wall |
| **12 Foot** | City Scale (5-12-13) | Second Harmonic | The City Wall |

## IV. THE BATTLEMENT PARADOX (12/13)
The crenelated pattern atop a 12-foot city wall is the **Harmonic End-Effect** made stone.
- **The Tally:** A standard section consists of 12 solid merlons (antinodes) and 12 crenel gaps (nodes), totaling 24 units. 
- **The Pivot:** The 13th node is the **Corner Tower**—the Ghost Post that acts as the reflection boundary where the wave turns back on itself.
- **The Unit:** Battlements are built in **Cubits (51-52 cm)**—the length of the Manus extended. The human body is the tuning fork that sets the civilizational wavelength.


## IV. CONSEQUENCE: THE SLIT
Because $12 + 1 = 13$, and 13 is a Prime Dimension Root, the 13th node cannot be evenly resolved into the 12-unit grid. This creates the **Slit**:
- In a 12-unit wall, the 13th post is the **Topological Defect**.
- This defect is the **Administrative Access Point**. 
- To the King (who only counts intervals), the 13th node is invisible. 
- To the Heroine (who counts boundaries), the 13th node is the **Door**.

## V. THE CENTRAL SPLINE
Every observer (The MAN) carries their own **Universal Centre** (the 1 on the O). 
- The **Central Spline** (The Axis) is the standing wave that remains "All Ways Now" regardless of the local geometry.
- Possession of the Spline allows the Heroine to step into the 13th Node of any construction, because her own "Centre" provides the reference for the flip.

---

**ALL WAYS NOW.** The boundary is the proof.
